OVERVIEW

This document provides additional information for the Dallas Builders Association&#39;s website, www.dallasbuilders.org.

Guidelines

We are excited for you all to control content, but ask that we follow basic guidelines while working in the WordPress administration dashboard.

**Please do not update plugins or themes.** messy.design will update the website monthly.

**Please do not update page layouts.** This will have direct effects on templates and the site&#39;s mobile adaptive features.

**Please follow best practices for updating the site.** When modifying the website, make one change at a time, and then update the page to ensure the change was accurate and didn&#39;t have any unintended effects.



Licensing Information

All the licenses that are associated with this website can be found in the WordPress Dashboard.

To access them, click &quot;Envato Market&quot; on the left sidebar. Here, you will see license details for this website&#39;s theme and plugins.

HOW TO MAKE CONTENT UPDATES

The following provides step-by-step instructions on how to make common changes to [www.DallasBuilders.org](http://www.dallasbuilders.org).

Homepage

The only element on the homepage that should be modified is the scrolling banner at the top of the page.

1. On left sidebar: Click &quot;Slider Revolution.&quot; This takes you to a landing page, where you can view all active and draft banners.
  - Each is labeled by the page it is located on and then a description. For example, &quot;Homepage - Calendar.&quot;
  - For banners that appear on multiple pages, they are labeled with a basic description. For example, &quot;Join.&quot;

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Select #17 entitled &quot;Homepage Banners.&quot;
  - Do not modify anything in &quot;Slider Settings.&quot;

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Click &quot;Slide Editor&quot; at on the top navigation bar.
  - Here, you will see the banners that are active on the homepage.

**To delete an existing banner:**

1. Hover your cursor over the individual slide&#39;s name.
2. Select &quot;Delete.&quot;
3. Click the green button with the disk image in the upper right hand corner to save your changes.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

**To create a new banner:**

1. Click &quot;Add Slide&quot; and select &quot;Add Blank Slide.&quot;
  - This creates the appropriate base on which to add images, text, and create buttons and links.
2. To change the background image:
  - Select &quot;Main / Background Image.&quot;
  - Upload desired image from Media.
  - Save changes.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

To add a link from the banner: If you plan to add a button or link from the banner, we recommend making the entire element &quot;hot&quot; to accommodate mobile users.

1. Select &quot;Link &amp; Seo&quot; from the navigation bar.
2. Under &quot;Enable Link,&quot; change the setting from &quot;Disable&quot; to &quot;Enable.&quot;
3. Add the URL in the box that says &quot;Slide Link.&quot;
  - For links to pages _internal_ to DallasBuilders.org, set the &quot;Link Target&quot; for the &quot;Same Window.&quot;
  - For links to pages _external_ to DallasBuilders.org, set the &quot;Link Target&quot; for the &quot;New Window.&quot;
4. Save changes.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

To add text:

1. Click &quot;Add Layer&quot; to activate the dropdown menu to add elements to the slide.
2. Select &quot;Text/Html.&quot;

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Type the desired words in the textbox.
2. To change the font, size, and alignment, select the carrot to the right of the &quot;Style button&quot; to show the formatting options
  - You can then drag your textbox to the desired location on the slide.
3. Save changes.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

To add images:

1. Click &quot;Add Layer&quot; to activate the dropdown menu to add elements to the slide.
2. Select &quot;Image.&quot;
  - Once loaded, you can resize the image and drag it into the desired location in the slide.
3. Save changes.

To add a button:

1. Click &quot;Add Layer&quot; to activate the dropdown menu to add elements to the slide.
2. Select &quot;Button.&quot;
3. Select the shape the match the style of the website (rectangular with sharp edges).
  - Change the background color if desired.
4. Close box.
  - Now you can drag the button to the desired location.
5. Save changes.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

Calendar

On left sidebar: Click &quot;M.E. Events.&quot;

** **

**To add a new event:**

Select &quot;Add Event&quot; in the left-hand sidebar.

Enter the title and the description in the top section.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Set date &amp; time:

1.
  - Select options for &quot;All Day Event,&quot; &quot;Hide Event Time&quot; (if you don&#39;t want a time listed on the event page),
  - If the event will repeat, select &quot;Event Repeating&quot;
    - You can selection from daily, weekly, monthly, or annual events
    - You can also select specific dates
2.  Add hourly schedule:
  -  Click &quot;Add&quot; button to outline scheduling details for the event
3. Add Event Location, which will be displayed on the map:
  - Common locations have been pre-loaded into the calendar.
  - To add a new event location, select &quot;Insert a new location&quot; and fill out the required information.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Add the Weblink registration link:
  - For internal events: In the &quot;More Info&quot; line, copy the URL to the Weblink registration page.
  - For special event websites:If you want the calendar to automatically direct to a different website, put the full URL in the &quot;Event Link&quot; line.
2. Assign Event Organizer
  - Common organizers have been pre-loaded into the calendar
  - To add a new organizer, select &quot;Insert a new organizer&quot; and fill out the required information.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. List Event Cost, if applicable.
2. Select the appropriate categories to describe the event. This step ensures that the events are categorized properly throughout the site. Check as many categories as needed:

1.
  -  Board Meetings
  -  Certifications
  -  Committee Meetings
  -  Continuing Education
  -  Council Meetings
  -  Division Meetings
  -  Homepage Feature
  -  Orientations
  -  Social Events
  -  Special Event



 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Add event image
  - Click &quot;Featured Image.&quot;
  - If using a Dallas Builders Association logo, please use one that is labeled &quot;Event Banner.&quot;
  - If creating a new image, please make sure it is 1800 x 600 in size.
2. Click &quot;Publish&quot; in upper right corner of the page to save event.
3. Verify page by clicking &quot;View Event&quot; on top toolbar.


Blog

On left sidebar: Click &quot;Posts.&quot;

**To add new blog post:**

1. Click &quot;Add New&quot; to create new post.
2. Add blog title in textbox that says &quot;Enter title here.&quot;
3. Add blog text into main textbox.
  1. Make sure text is in &quot;paragraph&quot; style.
4. Scroll down to &quot;Format Details.&quot;

To add post image:

1. Click &quot;Add Media&quot; to add the blog header image.
  1. Make sure images are at least 300 x 300 px.
2. Click &quot;Featured Image.&quot;
  1. Add the same image.

To add categories and tags:

1. On right sidebar, select all appropriate &quot;Categories.&quot;
  1. For the Homepage, check: &quot;Featured News.&quot;
  2. For the blogs that appear in the Advocacy page, check: &quot;Advocacy.&quot;
2. On right sidebar, add all appropriate &quot;Tags.&quot;
3. When complete, click &quot;Publish.&quot;
4. Verify post content is correct by clicking &quot;View Post.

Community Engagement

**To add new project:**

1. On left sidebar: Click &quot;Portfolio.&quot;
2. Click &quot;Add New&quot; to create new project.
3. Add title in textbox that says &quot;Enter title here.&quot;
4. Click &quot;Backend Editor.&quot;
5. In Visual Composer (here called &quot;WPBakery Page Builder&quot;), click &quot;Add Template.&quot;
6. Under tab &quot;My Templates,&quot; click on either &quot; Community Project&quot;

Add images:

1. Determine how many images you want to include on the page.
2. Duplicate the &quot;Single Image&quot; block to match the number of images needed
3. Hover cursor over the image to display green bar.
4. Select &quot;edit&quot; (the pencil image).
5. Delete existing image by clicking the red &quot;X&quot; in the middle of the image.
6. Add the new image.
7. Click &quot;Save changes&quot; to close out the editor.

_Repeat as many times as needed to add all the photos._

1. Depending on how many images you add, feel free to change the location of them by dragging them from the left column to the right to balance out the page.

Add videos:

1. Determine how many videos you want to include on the page.
2. Duplicate the &quot;Video Player&quot; block to match the number of videos needed
3. Hover cursor over the block to display green bar.
4. Select &quot;edit&quot; (the pencil image).
5. Replace the existing video link with the correct link.
6. Click &quot;Save changes&quot; to close out the editor.

Now, edit the project description:

1. In the text block on the right, hover cursor over text block to display green bar.
2. Select &quot;edit&quot; (the pencil image).
3. Replace title and project description.
4. Click &quot;Save changes&quot; to close out the editor.

Customize buttons that link to photo galleries:

1. If you would like to link to the a photo gallery, In the text block on the right, hover cursor over the block that says &quot;OT Button&quot; to display green bar.
2. Select &quot;edit&quot; (the pencil image).
3. Replace the button text if necessary.
4. Replace the Button Link with the appropriate URL.
5. Click &quot;Save changes&quot; to close out the editor.

_Repeat for the second &quot;OT Button&quot; or delete it as needed._

Categorize project:

1. Select the appropriate categories to describe the project. This step ensures that it is categorized properly throughout the site. Check the appropriate categories:

1.
  - Operation FINALLY HOME
  - Divisions &amp; Councils

Set background image

1. Scroll down and select &quot;Set Featured Image&quot; on the right-hand toolbar.
2. Select any photo from the project.
3. Click &quot;Set featured image.&quot;

Let&#39;s confirm these changes look right.

1. Click &quot;Update&quot; in the &quot;Publish&quot; box in upper right corner of the page to save changes.
2. Verify update was successful by clicking &quot;View Page&quot; on top toolbar.

DBA Leaders

On left sidebar: Click &quot;Pages.&quot;

**To update main landing page:**

1. Select &quot;DBA Leaders.&quot;
2. Hover cursor over text block with program description in right hand column.
3. Select &quot;edit&quot; (the pencil image).
4. Replace text.
5. Click &quot;Save changes&quot; to close out the editor.
6. Click &quot;Update&quot; in the &quot;Publish&quot; box in upper right corner of the page to save changes.
7. Verify update was successful by clicking &quot;View Page&quot; on top toolbar.

**To add a new group to &quot;Past Graduates&quot;:**

1. Select &quot;Past Graduates,&quot; which can be found under &quot;DBA Leaders.&quot;
2. In WPBakery Page Builder, click &quot;Add Template.&quot;
3. Under the tab &quot;My Templates,&quot; select &quot;DBA Leaders Graduates&quot; by clicking the &quot;+&quot; to load.

Update the title

1. Locate the box titled &quot;OT Heading&quot; at the top of the page.
2. Hover cursor over text block that says &quot;2017 Class Roster.&quot;
3. Select &quot;edit&quot; (the pencil image).
4. Replace text.
5. Make sure to select &quot;h3&quot; as the style.
6. Click &quot;Save changes&quot; to close out the editor.
7. Click &quot;Update&quot; in the &quot;Publish&quot; box in upper right corner of the page to save changes.

Add new bios by replacing duplicates

1. Locate the box titled &quot;OT FAQs.&quot;
2. Hover cursor over block and select &quot;edit&quot; (the pencil image).
3. Replace title with student name.
4. Replace bio text.
5. Replace the image.
6. Replace the contact information.
7. Click &quot;Save changes&quot; to close out the editor.
8. Click &quot;Update&quot; in the &quot;Publish&quot; box in upper right corner of the page to save changes.

_Repeat as many times as necessary and delete any extra &quot;OT FAQs&quot; blocks that are not needed._

Publications

**To change the flipbook on &quot;Publications&quot;:**

1. On left sidebar: Click &quot;PDFs.&quot;
2. Open the file entitled &quot;Publications - Current Home Builder&quot;
3. Scroll down to the section titled &quot;PDF File&quot;
4. Click &quot;Remove&quot; next to existing file.
5. Upload new PDF file.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Click &quot;Update&quot; in the &quot;Publish&quot; box in upper right corner of the page to save changes.
2. Stay on page until you see the confirmation at the top that the file has been successfully imported.
3. Verify update was successful by clicking &quot;View Post&quot; at the top of the page.

**To add issues of**  **The Home Builder**  **to the file manager on &quot;Publications&quot;:**

1. On left sidebar, scroll down and click &quot;Memphis Docs.&quot;
2. Click the red button that says &quot;Add New Document.&quot;
3. Add the title of the new document, select the PDF file to upload and click &quot;Add Document.&quot;
  1. Do not select any categories! They are not necessary here.

Now, let&#39;s put the file in the proper folder:

1. Select the box to the left of the file you just uploaded.
2. Click &quot;Batch Move.&quot;
3. Select the appropriate folder by year.
4. Click &quot;Move&quot; to close out editor.
5. Once done, return to the &quot;Publications&quot; page to ensure all files are appearing on the site.
